description:
&lt;p&gt;Do you have an interest in caring for patients in the critical care environment where learning, research, technological advances and innovation are central to high quality care?&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interested? Here is some information about our units:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We provide care for patients in the following specialities:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;General surgery, general medicine, solid organ transplant, burns, trauma, neuro medicine and surgery, liver medicine and surgery, maternity, renal, oncology, cardiology and cardiothoracic surgery.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Our service is ever expanding. These exciting changes within our pioneering and rapidly developing units will provide excellent opportunities for a Band 5 Staff Nurse to develop clinical skills with the right education and support.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We have a dedicated Critical Care Clinical Education Team who facilitate in-house and external education based on competencies and treatment developments.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Minimum requirements to apply:-&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;RN level 1 registration&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;post registration acute ward experience&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Why not come and see what our modern and purpose built critical care unit has to offer.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;At University Hospitals Birmingham we support flexible working and welcome applications from nurses seeking flexible working opportunities and family friendly working hours.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further information, please contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Joanna Gallimore, Clinical Educator Team Manager - Critical Care (joanna.gallimore@uhb.nhs.uk or 0121 371 2827/ 07795666306)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;or&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Louise Carter, Matron Critical Care Area A (louise.carter@uhb.nhs.uk or 0121 371 6321)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Mindy Dawes, Matron Critical Care Areas B and C (mindy.dawes@uhb.nhs.uk) or 0121 371 2578)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Ranj Patel, Matron Critical Care Area D (ranj.patel@uhb.nhs.uk or 0121 371 2805).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt; &lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;PLEAE NOTE THAT ALL INTERVIEWS WILL BE VIA VIDEO LINK DUE TO CURRENT PANDEMIC.&lt;/p&gt;
